-- Nike CEO Parker earns $1.25 million salary in 2007
-- 
-- Fri Aug 3, 2007 6:51pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/08/03/us-nike-ceocompensation-idUSN0343770920070803

 

 LOS ANGELES  (Reuters) - Nike Inc ( NKE.N ) Chief Executive Mark Parker earned $1.25 million in salary in fiscal 2007, according to a filing, his first full fiscal year as head of the global athletic shoe company. 

 Parker, who was named CEO early last year, also received more than $2.1 million through the company's incentive plan, as well as profit-sharing contributions and perks totaling less than $200,000, according to a filing with the U.S. Securities & Exchange Commission. During fiscal 2007, Parker also exercised $7.38 million in option awards and vested $1.2 million in stock awards. For fiscal 2006, Parker was paid a salary of $1.14 million, received a bonus of $1.29 million and received more than $2 million in restricted stock awards and other compensation. Before becoming CEO, Parker served as co-president of the Nike brand.